Songkhla authorities have expanded an investigation into the smuggling of more than 200 illegal immigrants recently found in the southern province to find the masterminds behind the smuggling racket. Songkhla governor Kritsada Boonrach yesterday said he has ordered Songkhla police to extend their inquiries. Warrants were issued for the arrest of two people involved in the smuggling of Rohingya immigrant people last month. This article is older than 60 days, which we reserve for our premium members only. You can subscribe to our premium member subscription, here. 